  <locationDescription><![CDATA[<p>A multi-centre holiday lets you mix and match hotels, lengths of stay, and exciting activities to create your ideal trip. Enjoy everything from guided walks and outdoor adventures to relaxing seaside days and tasty local cuisine.</p>
<p><strong>Explore Montecatini on foot (or by funicular)</strong></p>
<p>From the thermal spas of Montecatini Terme and up to the ancient cobbled streets of Montecatini Alto. If Tuscan postcard views are what you're looking for, then the panoramas from the top are perfetto. Join our guided walk up to Montecatini Alto and discover them for yourself, or head up on Montecatini's funicular (guided walks run on selected days). As you explore, why not go further afield to Lucca and learn about the ancient Roman Nottolini Aqueduct. End your days sipping local Tuscan wine and nibbling on cured meats and delicious cheeses from the region.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/ddef5c7c9bdb475792ae27614a6308b8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ddef5c7c9bdb475792ae27614a6308b8}" title="Montecatini" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Montecatini</a></p>
<p><strong>Relax by the sea in Liguria and indulge in Pesto Genovese and Limoncello</strong></p>
<p>The Cinque Terre and the Portofino areas have a rich history and culture, as well as out-of-this-world coastal views and sea side promenades. The capital city of Genova is famous for pesto Genovese and was once home to Italy's famous revolutionary, Giuseppe Garibaldi. Walk along cliff paths in the Cinque Terre and gaze out at the glistening Mediterranean sea. Sip limoncello at sunset, eat freshly caught fish and drink an espresso by Portofino Harbour. Or, discover Portofino's rich art scene and wander through the Portofino Natural Park in your walking boots, hopping from town to town on the Cinque Terre's train network; see if you can find any vineyards to stop in as you explore.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb}" title="Liguria" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Liguria</a></p>
<p><a href="tel:01483791111" class="InfinityNumber c-btn">Call Us to Book Today</a></p>]]></locationDescription>
